      "explanation": "Ṣé in front of a statement makes a yes/no question: Ṣé o fẹ́ omi? (Do you want water?). Content questions use kí ni (what), ta ni (who), níbo (where): Kí ni orúkọ rẹ? (What is your name?), Níbo lo ń lọ? (Where are you going?).",
