      "explanation": "Possessive pronouns follow the noun: ìwé mi (my book), ilé rẹ (your house), ọkọ̀ rẹ̀ (his/her vehicle), ilé wa (our house). Between two nouns, possession is just order (or ti): ilé bàbá (father's house).",
